      • decodeStatement

        public static Literal decodeStatement(Node parent,
                                      java.lang.String statement,
                                      Location location,
                                      boolean require)
        Decode the given statement into a Literal instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.
        Example inputs include:
        • 123
        • -321
        • 121.32
        • 'a'
        • '\''
        • "Text String"
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a Literal instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a Literal.
